text: Isojärvi National Park () is a national park in Central Finland. It covers 19 square kilometers (7.3 sq mi) and was founded in 1982. Its vegetation is dominated by Scots pine and Norway spruce forests. Evidence has been found of early human settlements in the area. == References == Category:1980s establishments in Finland Category:1982 establishments in Europe Category:National parks in Finland
